    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1879-08-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1879-08-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="334"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d334">
                <head>No. 306.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bingham</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Evarts</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">United States Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tokei, Japan</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1879-08-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 29, 1879</date>. (Received September
                        29.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 944.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Herewith I have the honor to inclose for your:
                    information the official statement of the statistics of Asiatic cholera within
                    this empire, up to the 26th instant, from which it appears that the total number
                    of cases to that date was 102,217, and that of this number 54,615 died; showing
                    a mortality of over 50 per cent.</p>
                <p>I inclose herewith a copy of the statement kindly furnished me by his excellency
                    Mr. Ito. His Imperial Japanese Majesty’s Minister of the Interior. You will note
                    that all this mortality from cholera has happened within the last four
                    months.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JNO. A. BINGHAM.</signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No. 944.—Cholera statics,
                            1879.]</seg>
                    </opener>
