                    </table>
                    <p>The localities that have been the most seriously affected by this disease are
                        as follows: The Ishikawa, Okayama, Yéhime, Sakai, Kumamoto, Yamaguchi, and
                        Oita Kens. The number of patients in each of these <pb facs="0778" n="682"
                            xml:id="pg_682"/> kens has varied from 3,000 to 14,000, and the
                        percentage of mortality has reached 53 per cent. In Osaca the percentage was
                        77 per cent. The Miyagi and the Iwata Kens have happily escaped visitation
                        by the cholera, and they are the only ones that have.</p>
